<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="195" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1700,1866]" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">
Diagnosis:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Al-Shehbaz" authorityYear="2022" box="[263,427,1700,1721]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Heliophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verna">
<emphasis box="[263,427,1700,1721]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="195">Heliophila verna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is readily distinguished from the other glabrous annual congeners with filiform leaves and submoniliform terete fruit by having fruiting pedicels 
<quantity box="[558,637,1736,1757]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
long, smallest flowers (petals to 
<quantity box="[954,1027,1736,1758]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
long), slender and cylindrical styles 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="195" unit="mm" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.3 mm</quantity>
wide, and 14–18 ovules per ovary.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
